creator: Maria Edgeworth
description:
LibriVox recording of Helen by Maria Edgeworth.
Read in English by Terra Mendoza; add1sun; Jenny Bradshaw; Jennifer Woodside; Michele Eaton; Lynne Thompson; MaryAnn; Linda Andrus; diaz2010; John Burlinson; Kathleen Moore; Jothi Tharavant
Helen is the story of a young orphan left penniless by her guardian. Invited into the home of her once childhood friend Cecilia Davenant, now newly married to General Clarendan. Helen enjoys the company of her friend and Lady Davenant, Cecilia's wise mother who takes Helen under her wing. Lady Davenant has a deep love and respect for Helen that sometimes appears to go beyond her love for her own child. Their relationship grows as they spend time together, but Lady Davenant is soon taken away due to her husband's new position as ambassador at the Court of St. Petersburg, Russia. Helen is left to the devices of her friend Cecilia who has unfortunately had an affair prior to her marriage that she kept a secret from her husband. This affair is brought to General Clarendan's attention through a packet of letters he receives, which Cecilia implores Helen to claim as her own. Through this entire situation Helen's name and reputation is left in shreds and her engagement is ended. The story culminates with Lady Davenant's return. She is deathly ill, and upon her return the truth has finally come out with General Clarendan's declaration that he will separate for life from his wife. Lady Davenant's illness and presence finally brings about repentance from Cecilia and the betrayal is forgiven. The novel ends with all protaganists coming to a happy conclusion. ( Summary by Terra Mendoza )
